Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,hovercraft: n.  气垫船\N\NLesson 29 The hovercraft\N\N气垫船\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.01,0:00:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,First listen and then answer the following question.\N\N听录音,然后回答以下问题.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.32,0:00:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,hovercraft: n.  气垫船\N\NWhat is a hovercraft riding on when it is in motion?\N\N气垫船靠什么行驶?\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.19,0:00:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Many strange new means of transport have been developed in our century,\N\N本世纪已研制出许多新奇的交通工具,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.82,0:00:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,hovercraft: n.  气垫船\N\Nthe strangest of them being perhaps the hovercraft.\N\N其中最新奇的要数气垫船了.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.02,0:00:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1953,a former electronics engineer in his fifties, Christopher Cockerell,\N\N1953年,有一位50多岁名叫克里斯托弗.科克雷尔的原电子工程师,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.73,0:00:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Norfolk Broads: n.  诺福克郡的湖泊地区\N\Nwho had turned to boat-building on the Norfolk Broads,\N\N改行在诺福克郡的湖泊地区从事造船业,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.62,0:00:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,suggested an idea on which he had been working for many years to the British Government and industrial circles.\N\N他提出了他研究多年的一项计划给英国政府和工业界.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.27,0:00:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,cushion: n.  座垫\N\NIt was the idea of supporting a craft on a 'pad',or cushion, of lowpressure air,\N\N他的设想是:用一个低压空气垫或软垫来支撑船体\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.66,0:00:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,ring: v.  围\N\Nringed with a curtain of higher pressure air.\N\N软垫周围用高压空气环绕.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.96,0:00:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since,people have had difficulty in deciding\N\N自那以后,人们很难决定\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.42,0:01:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,whether the craft should be ranged among ships,planes, or land vehicles--\N\N是否应该将这种运载工具列为轮船、飞机,或是陆上交通工具,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.12,0:01:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,for it is something in between a boat and an aircraft.\N\N因为它是介于船和飞机之间一种东西.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.29,0:01:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,As a shipbuilder,\N\N作为一个船舶技师,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.32,0:01:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Cockerell was trying to find a solution to the problem of the wave resistance\N\N科克雷尔在寻找解决波浪阻力的方法,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.42,0:01:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,which wastes a good deal of a surface ship's power and limits its speed.\N\N波浪阻力浪费掉了船在水面行驶的大量动力,从而限制了船的速度.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.83,0:01:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,His answer was to lift the vessel out of the water\N\N他的解决办法是把船体提离水面,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.85,0:01:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,cushion: n.  座垫\N\Nby making it ride on a cushion of air,no more than one or two feet thick.\N\N让船在一个气垫上行驶,气垫只有一两英尺厚.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.06,0:01:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,ring: v.  围\N\NThis is done by a great number of ringshaped air jets on the bottom of the craft.\N\N船底装上大量环状气嘴以实现这一目的.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.54,0:01:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It 'flies',therefore, but it cannot fly higher--\N\N这样,船就能飞了,但飞不高.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.74,0:01:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,its action depends on the surface,water or ground,over which it rides.\N\N它的飞行取决于它所悬浮的水面或地面.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.97,0:01:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Solent: n.  （英国的）苏伦特海峡, sensation: n.  轰动\N\NThe first tests on the Solent in 1959 caused a sensation.\N\N959年,在苏伦特海峡进行的首次试航引起了轰动.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.13,0:02:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,hovercraft: n.  气垫船\N\NThe hovercraft travelled first over the water,then mounted the beach,\N\N气垫船先是在水面上行驶后又登上海岸,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.03,0:02:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,dune: n.  沙丘\N\Nclimbed up the dunes, and sat down on a road\N\N爬上沙丘,最后停在路上.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.02,0:02:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Later it crossed the Channel,riding smoothly over the waves,\N\N后来气垫船跨越英吉利海峡,平稳地在波浪上方行驶,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.13,0:02:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,which presented no problem.\N\N波浪不再产生阻力.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.06,0:02:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Since that time,\N\N从那以后,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.09,0:02:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,hovercraft: n.  气垫船\N\Nvarious types of hovercraft have appeared and taken up regular service.\N\N各种各样的气垫船出现了并开始了定期航行服务.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.14,0:02:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,hovercraft: n.  气垫船\N\NThe hovercraft is particularly useful in large areas with poor communications\N\N气垫船在交通不发达地区特别有用,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.70,0:02:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,such as Africa or Australia;\N\N象非洲、澳大利亚等地;\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.51,0:02:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it can become a 'flying fruit-bowl',\N\N它能成为"飞行水果盘子"\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.76,0:02:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,plantation: n.  种植园\N\Ncarrying bananas from the plantations to the ports;\N\N把香蕉从种植园运到港口\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.08,0:02:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,hovercraft: n.  气垫船\N\Ngiant hovercraft liners could span the Atlantic;\N\N大型的气垫班轮或许能跨越大西洋.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.27,0:02:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,hovertrain: n.  气垫火车\N\Nand the railway of the future may well be the 'hovertrain',\N\N未来的火车或许能成为"气垫火车",\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.01,0:02:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,cushion: n.  座垫\N\Nriding on its air cushion over a single rail,which it never touches,\N\N靠气垫在单轨上行驶而不接触轨道,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.91,0:02:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,at speeds,up to 300 m.p.h.--the possibilities appear unlimited.\N\N时速可达每小时300英里.气垫船的前途是不可限量的.\N\N